OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FAfternoon
OL,6,Fsunshine persisting into the overnight
OL,7,Fperiod before cloud pushes westward,
OL,8,Freaching the far east of the region
OL,9,Fand over higher ground. Otherwise a
OL,10,Fmostly clear night for all with brisk
OL,11,Fwinds on higher hills. Rural frost
OL,12,Fpossible.
OL,13,
OL,14,CThursday:FAny patchy cloud will clear
OL,15,Fquickly, leaving another bright and
OL,16,Fsunny day. Winds lighter than
OL,17,FWednesday allowing temperatures to
OL,18,Fclimb further. UV levels will also be
OL,19,Fhigh.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
